  "wikitext": "\n'''4-2-325\n\nPolarization error (in bearing)\n\nAn error, in an observed bearing, which varies with the state of polarization of the received waves relative to the designed plane of polarization.\n\n\nNote: Some types of polarization error may be attributable to specific features of the site (e.g. inclined conductors) and, as such, are also site errors.\n\nReference: B.S. (modified)\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Polarization error}}\n[[Category:4.2 Radio Beacons and Direction Finding Equipment]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
